The paper deals with Private Information Retrieval (PIR) which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves privacy and security (cs.CR) as the user wants to download messages without revealing any information to the server. The use of side information and codes suggests that it may also fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of previous interactions with the server and the use of random subsets of messages suggests that it may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
